main event: A witness observed a large, bright object that hovered and maneuvered in an erratic manner over Overton, Nevada on June 25, 1965.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be traveling at a speed of 600 mph.
The witness stated the object appeared to change course and position rapidly in a strange manner.
No photographs were taken of the object.
The Air Force concluded the sighting was likely an upper air research balloon that was being destroyed.
The Air Force thanked the witness for reporting the observation, stating it would assist in understanding the instrument packages associated with these types of projects.
result: Likely an upper air research balloon
